/tr><tr><td class="county-cell">McDowell</td><td>Thomas Bell</td><td>Home (304) 436-6976 / Cell (304) 888-1546</td></tr><tr><td class="county-cell" rowspan="2">Mineral</td><td>Rodney Taylor</td><td>Cell (304) 668-3411</td></tr><tr><td>Deven Barron</td><td>Cell (304) 886-2320</td></tr><tr><td class="county-cell">Monongalia</td><td>Mike Foley</td><td>Cell (304) 612-1304</td></tr><tr><td class="county-cell" rowspan="2">Morgan</td><td>Janet Nesselerodt</td><td>Cell (304) 279-5578</td></tr><tr><td>Anita Trout</td><td>Cell (304) 279-9289</td></tr><tr><td class="county-cell" rowspan="4">Nicholas</td><td>Fred Hart</td><td>Home (304) 640-1230</td></tr><tr><td>Ricky Moye</td><td>Cell (304) 228-3684</td></tr><tr><td>Michael Peck</td><td>Cell (304) 573-3935</td></tr><tr><td>Dave Shrader</td><td>Cell (304) 719-3811</td></tr><tr><td class="county-cell" rowspan="2">Ohio</td><td>Arthur Lightner</td><td>Home (304) 639-1866</td></tr><tr><td>Mark Cain</td><td>Cell (304) 4672 or (304) 281-6909</td></tr><tr><td class="county-cell" rowspan="2">Pendleton</td><td>Rodney Taylor</td><td>Cell (304) 668-3411</td></tr><tr><td>Deven Barron</td><td>Cell (304) 886-2320</td></tr><tr><td class="county-cell">Pleasants</td><td>Wayne Nichols</td><td>Home (304) 684-9502 / Cell (304) 917-5112</td></tr><tr><td class="county-cell" rowspan="2">Preston</td><td>Mike Foley</td><td>Cell (304) 612-1304</td></tr><tr><td>Blain Bowmar</td><td>Cell (304) 892-4649</td></tr><tr><td class="county-cell" rowspan="4">Raleigh</td><td>Fred Hart</td><td>Cell (304) 640-1230</td></tr><tr><td>Ricky Moye</td><td>Cell (304) 228-3684</td></tr><tr><td>Michael Peck</td><td>Cell (304) 573-3935</td></tr><tr><td>Dave Shrader</td><td>Cell (304) 719-3811</td></tr><tr><td class="county-cell" rowspan="2">Randolph</td><td>Tim Myers</td><td>Home (304) 478-4420 / Cell (304) 642-4424</td></tr><tr><td>Wesley Mole</td><td>Cell (304) 516-9844</td></tr><tr><td class="county-cell" rowspan="2">Upshur</td><td>Sam Criss</td><td>Cell (304) 476-0819</td></tr><tr><td>Tim Myers</td><td>Home (304) 478-4420 / Cell (304) 642-4424</td></tr><tr><td class="county-cell" rowspan="2">Wood</td><td>Wayne Nichols</td><td>Home (304) 684-9502 / Cell (304) 917-5112</td></tr><tr><td>Daniel Taylor</td><td>Home (304) 863-8806</td></tr></tbody><!-- Wood --><!-- Upshur --><!-- Randolph --><!-- Raleigh --><!-- Preston --><!-- Pleasants --><!-- Pendleton --><!-- Ohio --><!-- Nicholas --><!-- Morgan --><!-- Monongalia --><!-- Mineral --><!-- McDowell --><!-- Mason --><!-- Marion --><!-- Lewis --><!-- Kanawha --><!-- Jefferson --><!-- Jackson --><!-- Harrison --><!-- Hardy --><!-- Hancock --><!-- Greenbrier --><!-- Cabell --><!-- Brooke --><!-- Boone --><!-- Berkeley --></table></div></div><!-- DOT Physical – Medical Examiner's Certificate (MEC) --><div class="info-block mb-3" id="section-mec"><div class="info-block-header"><a style="color:inherit;text-decoration:none;" href="https://transportation.wv.gov/DMV/Motor-Carriers/CDL/Pages/default.aspx#collapseFourteen">DOT Physical – Medical Examiner's Certificate (MEC)&nbsp;</a></div><div class="info-block-body"><p>A licensee who lists their self-certification status as a non-excepted status (NI or NA) must maintain a valid FMCSA <a href="https://www.fmcsa.dot.gov/regulations/medical/medical-examiners-certificate-commercial-driver-medical-certification" target="_blank">Medical Examiner's Certificate (MEC)</a> on file with the DMV. The DOT physical must be completed by a certified medical examiner listed on the <a href="https://nationalregistry.fmcsa.dot.gov/home" target="_blank">FMCSA's National Registry website</a>.</p><p>Any West Virginia CDL holder who fails to maintain proof of a valid MEC with the DMV will have their CDL medical status downgraded to <strong>NOT-CERTIFIED</strong> ten (<strong>10</strong>) days after the current MEC expires. Federal guidelines mandate that if a valid MEC is not provided to the DMV within <strong>30 days</strong> after expiration, the CDL license will be downgraded to a <strong>Class E Driver's License</strong>, which is a non-CDL and allows for the operation of non-commercial vehicles only.</p><p>All MECs must be submitted electronically by the medical provider conducting the physical.*</p><p>We request that you verify the certificate has been provided by the medical examiner and updated by contacting the CDL Unit at <strong>(304) 926-3801</strong> or by using the online services to <a href="https://apps.wv.gov/DMV/SelfService/DrivingRecord" target="_blank">check the CDL status</a>.</p><p>Any certificate more than <strong>two (2) years</strong> old is not current. Any certificate that is valid less than <strong>30 days</strong> cannot be accepted.</p><div class="notes-block"><p>* FMCSA granted a waiver allowing interstate commercial driver's license (CDL) holders, commercial learner's permit (CLP) holders, and motor carriers to continue relying on paper copies of medical examiner's certificates as proof of drivers' medical certification for up to 15 days after the date the medical examiner's certificate is issued. The waiver is in effect until <strong>October 12, 2025</strong>, and a copy of the waiver is available on <a href="https://nationalregistry.fmcsa.dot.gov/assets/resource-center/FINAL%20NRII%20Waiver%207-14-2025.pdf" target="_blank">FMCSA's website</a>.</p></div></div></div><!-- Back to Top Button --><p><button class="back-to-top" id="backToTop" title="Back to top" onclick="window.scrollTo({ top: 0, behavior: &apos;smooth&apos; })">
